If you are into business you will learn a lot from him, as he is very knowledgeable.  As long as you always attend class, particapte often, and study you should do well. Always lets you know exactly what he expects from you. Overall a great guy.
Professor Power is very controlling. He is always in charge. Make sure you go to class and stay awake. Study and give your input and you will do fine.
Great Teacher, very helpful, outlines and specifies all material that is needed, no gimmicks, go to class, study a little, and you should do great.
No Comments

If you like any aspect of business, you will be tuned-in to the class the entire time.  You will have to do work, that will take time, but you will learn. Go to class, do work, and participate, and you will be happy. This guy is great.
Great teacher

Incredible Professor. Explained everything perfectly, and gave enough examples for us to solve any homework assignment. If this wasn't enough, he was very easy to reach outside of the class, and super nice about any questions we may have. Can't recommend enough!
He is just the goat. Very good at teaching as well as a genuine caring person. One of my best classes so far!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Clear grading criteria--Amazing lectures

comment: DS4300 with Prof. Rachlin was definitely my favorite class I've taken at Northeastern. His lectures focus on topics that he thinks students will find interesting or helpful. He also seems like he genuinely wants to see his students succeed, and will make time outside of class to offer guidance, career advice, etc. Couldn't recommend more!

Rachlin is a very good teacher. I had him asynchronously during COVID, but his lectures were so clear that I had absolutely no trouble keeping up. He gives you a huge amount of examples that he fully solves for you, so any exam or quiz is easy to study for because it's essentially the same problems. Very nice guy, easy grader, highly recommend.
Best professor Ive had here so far by a lot. Amazing guy, gives great lectures, made the class very doable for those with no prior coding experience, and clearly cares/is passionate about teaching.

Professor Rachlin is a GREAT lecturer. If you attend his lectures and go to office hours you WILL get an A in his class. I had NO coding experience when I took DS 2000 and as a Data Science major I can say that he inspired me to continue my study of data science. He's very passionate in a quirky but funny way and is accessible outside of class.

I took this class completely virtual, and Professor Rachlin is one of the best professors I have had at NEU! He teaches Python in a very accessible and engaging way, I never thought that I would like it so much. He clearly puts in a ton of prep time to every single lecture. He answers every question on Piazza, and is always helpful and available

Prof. Rachlin's lectures were sometimes dry but my class was 1 hr and 40 minutes so and it was more a reflection of the material. He is an amazing guy and you are in good hands taking his course. He rewards for effort and is one of the most helpful, genuine, down to earth people I've met. If you get the opportunity to take a class with him, do it.

Widely regarded as one of the top CS professors at NU. Sadly, he is also regarded as the ONLY good DB design professor (at least during my year) - so you probably don't need to be convinced to try and take this with him. Funny, clear, smart, relatable, compassionate - a breath of fresh air in the Northeastern CS department.

Very rude. While I did well in the course, I will NOT take another class with him. Lacks compassion and is very unreasonable when asking for clarification on grading. Lectures are extremely boring, and a lot of the material can be self taught better than his explanations. Take someone else if at all possible, and if you can't then GOOD LUCK.

Had him for recitation and have him now for database and, while the class is online right now, is one of the best professors I've had. You can tell he really cares about teaching. Sometimes he'll go off on tangents but he's still a great teacher who's very understandable.

Great guy with interesting lectures. Really cares about student understanding. Patient and considerate of students experience with the material. Very excited to be in class and explaining new things to students. Would recommend taking this course.

Professor Rachlin is amazing. You won't be super entertained in all of his lectures, but he makes the material seem less daunting, and explains it well. He is one of the most genuine, caring professors I have ever had. On the last day of class, he puts together a presentation about his life lessons and it's the cutest thing ever. Highly recommend.
Great professor with clear grading criteria. Would definitely take this class again. Difficult to get an A because it's a 95+, but an A- is easily possible.

Rachlin really cares about his students and is always accessible. He tries to make the topics interesting and relevant and he makes a lot of dad jokes. I would really recommend taking his classes because I think he will help you will be more successful than if you took them with another professor.

Great professor who really cares about his students. Has a deep interest in the curriculum and shows it during lectures. While the material can be dry at times, he is able to keep things interesting and funny. Would recommend taking 1800 with Rachlin.

You won't find an easier class at Northeastern than PSCY 1101 by Prof. Weine. Funny and kind and care, she will keep things simple for you and make sure you enjoy learning about the subject! SUPER EASY AND FUN!
Super easy, just do all the assignments and you should pass just fine.

Dr. Weine is a great professor. The work load isn't heavy. All of the lectures are recorded and followed by assignment which is usually 2-4 questions long. She's really passionate about the class, and she makes the lectures interesting.

A pretty simple class with one assignment per lecture (only 2-4 Qs) that is due when next quiz is due. Quizzes are easy and straight from lecture as are exams. Prof is super enthusiastic and laid back. Attendance was just a word of the day that you could get from peers if you didnt go to lecture. Loved Dr. Weine and her teaching method!

Nice professor. Overly easy, zero effort, which is usually good, but it ultimately wasn't challenging at all, underwhelming, and somewhat boring. Most of coursework was simple quizzes and weekly assignments. Easy A.

Dr. Weine really cares about psychology and you can tell from her lectures. She's straightforward, but also willing to indulge students questions. She's passionate, funny, and definitely makes class interesting. The tests weren't that difficult and the questions came straight from lecture material. Definitely recommend!

I don't have enough space to say how much I love Prof. Weine here. Literally, the best. Such an engaging, funny lecturer. You don't have to show up to class, genuinely all you need to know is in the powerpoints. If you can take her. class, DO IT. She's so caring and great. Not much homework, no reading, and an easy A. You. need to experience her.

Prof Weine is super fun; she loves what she does. Shes always so up beat in her lectures. You dont actually have to go to the lectures to do well: all the info u need is in the powerpoints. Pretty easy to get an A in the class: 5 quizzes (40%) & midterm (15%) that help you prepare for the final (15%).

Professor Weine has been one of the most caring and entertaining professors I've ever had. She keeps her lectures extremely engaging and fun even when the material starts to get a little dull. Homework is very light and quizzes and tests are all multiple choice and easy as long as you pay attention in class. Highly recommend for PSYC1101.

Prof. Weine is by FAR my favourite professor! Her lectures are captivating, even in a class I wasn't too PSYCHed about (srry), and she genuinely wants her students to succeed. Slides are posted, but lectures are really fun and helpful! Weekly 2-3 question assignments and 10 question quizzes, but they're A BREEZE and seriously set you up for success

Weine was a great professor who made lectures engaging. Weekly assignments (basically worksheets) took less than an hour to complete and helped boost your grade. As with any psych course there was a lot of material covered. Make flashcards and you will be fine. Midterm and final worth 15% each, both are multiple choice.

Nearly no complaints about this class-pretty interesting, easy A with bare minimum effort, Weine is super nice. Only complaint would be that she is nearly impossible to get in contact with, expect emails to not get responses for days, if ever, even if they're the simplest questions. But outside of that highly recommend it

Professor Weine is a great teacher. I'm not a psych major, I just took this to be an easy elective, but I ended up finding a lot of the subject interesting. I recommend going to class because she is good at giving applicable examples that will be on quizzes/tests. Quizzes and exams were decent as long as you make flashcards.

The class was a standard intro course, which felt overly easy. Professor was friendly and clear, but it was too simplistic and I felt like I was in a high school class again. I wanted to be challenged much more.

For PSYC1101 It was 15% final, 15% Midterm, 30% Weekly Worksheets (No more than an hour at best) and 40% Biweekly Quizzes. All exams and quizzes are multiple choice and very fair. For Foundations of Psych it was a great introductory course and she was cool enough to not require a textbook which saves a lot of money. 5/5 Made my semester fun

Prof Weine is definitely the best of the best. She is super nice and gives amazing lectures. Midterm and Final not that difficult if you review the slides carefully, and each of them only worths 15% of the grade. I hope to take another class with Prof Weine, but she only teaches PSYC 1101 and PSYC 3404

By far the sweetest and funniest professor I've had. I became a psych major because of her class. So fun and interesting, and not at all challenging. She truly is so caring and passionate about the subject. Please take her class, I promise you won't regret it.

She's. The Best. Prof. Weine is so funny and such an honest, good person. I'm not a psych student but am considering a psych minor, and I'm sad she's a rather new professor because I'd take 5 of her classes if I could. She answers any question, no matter how stupid, makes easy tests - and no attendance, but honestly, I don't want to miss her class.

She's very bright and positive; definitely one of the most pleasant professors I've had. She organizes the course in such a way that you don't have to come on Thursdays, even though it's on the schedule, as that is assignment day. The assignments are straightforward, and help boost your grade. Overall, I highly recommend taking a class with her!

Professor Weine was one of the sweetest professors I've ever had at Northeastern. She is extremely caring about her students and always made things clear for her students. The class has a lot of discussion so you have to participate, but usually the articles she gives us are easy to say a few things about.
I had her for Developmental Psychology and she is hands down the best professor I've had so far. If you get a chance to take a psychology course with her as the professor, you really should.

Erienne Weine is the best teacher I have ever had!!! I pity everyone who has never taken a class with her. She explains thing very well, and wants all of her students to succeed. If you go to the lectures it an easy A. Even if you don't go to the lectures and just use her slides you will pass the class. But go to her lectures 'cause she is the GOAT

I had her for a summer session of Developmental. I went into the class dreading the subject, thinking I would hate it, but she was such an amazing lecturer that I was instantly hooked! She was always throwing in fun personal (but IMPORTANTLY not oversharing) stories to supplement the material. She just gave the whole experience such a great vibe.
Her tests and midterms are only mcq's and are easy. She's lively in class and you can get a class off a week to do assignments rom home.

Best prof. ever!! She highly enjoys what she does and provides so many examples that it is almost impossible to not understand the material. Attendance is not mandatory but I never wanted to miss a single class. Recommend her to everyone!!

A real gem. She is an AMAZING teacher & loves what she does. She legit says "this is so cool" a million times in class, i was genuinely EXCITED to go to class. She actually cares & wants you to succeed. Gives loads of quizzes+discussions but if you actually try,you'll be fine. Fair grader,sweetest prof on earth & very respected! Love her. A++ prof!
You must participate in 6 hours of psychological studies.

She is an amazing teacher, really cares about her students and her class is SO EASY. Only open notes tests and assignments -- no final, no midterm, nothing. You don't have to go to class to do well but you'll want to go to see her and listen to her because she's amazing. HIGHLY RECOMMEND HER. I took her for Developmental Psychology
Absolutely recommended! her class is fun and you learn so much just by showing up! lots of quizzes, but no midterm or final. Very easy and fun class. Very willing to help students. TAKE HER CLASS!!!
Only Facts- his classes are small, full of discussions, regular and simple assignments, individual-based, and engaging. He is a hidden gem, take him if you want an easy A with a lot of fun!

As long as you show up to class and show an interest in the material you will pass. He is a great professor, and really works to engage the students. He gives thoughtful assignments and will not waste your time. I really liked him, and would definitely take this class again.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Graded by few things

comment: Best professor! He is really engaged in class and he cares a lot about the students. Gives great feedback and is not a hard grader. just make sure you actually show up to class
Hes literally the best. Class was easy and always fun. As long as you do the work, you will do well in the class. You MUST take a class with him. One of my all time favorites.

Professor Stockman was awesome. The class was so fun and enjoyable because of his personality. He's also very understanding. Participation and attendance matters. He doesn't give you a grade until the semester is over so that may be a problem for some as you can't really know how well you're doing. I don't see why I wouldn't get an A though.

He is super funny and inspirational. There are only like three or four essays throughout the semester and he cares a lot about participation. Also there is a blog you have to write every week, which is pretty easy.

Stockman is literally the best professor I have had at Northeastern. He wants you to focus on actually learning rather than grades! His class is an easy A! Just come to class, it is discussion based so be ready to participate, and do everything the syllabus says. It may be a service learning course so be ready to spend about 2 hours a week on it.
ratingTags: Respected--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Mo Taslim is by far one of the most disrespectful and unfair professors I've had. Do not take his course, even if it means taking Fluids another semester. comment: Oyelaran is AMAZING. She's incredibly smart and pushes her students to fully understand the content.

She teaches well, and her lecture style is great. She gives you lecture outlines that you fill out during class (you need colored pens - you're going to do A LOT of color coding) and uploads her lecture recordings on Tegrity. HOWEVER, her exams (2 midterms, 25 Q, multiple choice) can be difficult and her final is simply IMPOSSIBLE. Be ware.

Oyelaran is great. After taking gen chem I and II with toher, I found that Oyelaran was a little clearer, possibly as a result from her great notes system. She also puts every lecture on tegrity, to worst case scenario, if you cant make it to class, you can catch up on tegrity. Very clear, knows her stuff, and expects you to care.

Oyelaran is tough and intimidating in a 1-to-1 conversation, but she is a nice person and is a great teacher. Her notes system (she calls them shells) make everything SO much easier to understand, and it forces you to pay attention because you have to write things out in between spaces. Tests aren't too bad but they are very tricky so be careful.
GO to class, and office hours!

Professor Oyelaran is THE BEST organic chemistry professor that I know of at Northeastern. She is an amazing teacher and explains everything well. Her tests are challenging, but not impossible. She can be a little intimidating in office hours, so make sure you have good questions prepared when you go that you absolutely cannot find the answers to.

Professor Oyelaran was the best teacher I've had at Northeastern University!  I had her both for organic chemistry 1 and 2, and each semester she was extremely effective and taught the material amazingly well.  She focuses on having you understand the principles over memorizing them. You learn the material a lot better that way -  A+ professor

Dr. O makes herself really available to help. She's one of the only teachers I know who has office hours daily and review sessions weekly. Excellent teacher. Highly recommend her for orgo 2 especially.
she is not that good of a teacher but she is the best for orgo1. The best thing she does is that she gives out handouts for every class so you wouldnt have to write everything.

I had her for orgo1. I was so nervous going into the class because I heard the horrors of Organic Chem. She made the class interesting and easy to follow. She even provides outlines of her notes! To do good in the class, you really need to do practice problems and study her notes.

OChem is one of the most difficult classes in college. Professor Oyelaran is one of the best professors I've had so far. Very clear, informative lectures. Very caring about students, and gives all support for success. Nonetheless, she expects you to work. She definitely made OChem 2 interesting for me. Great experience.

Professor Oyelaran has a very clear, concise method of teaching, making her an efficient Organic Chemistry teacher. The course is as tough as you can expect Orgo to be but she gives you what you need to succeed. The exams I found were a bit tricky, but she sets the "B" range at the average of the class. Overall, a good professor.
She cares about her students.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Participation matters--So many papers

comment: I never hated so much by a professor as I felt by her. One wrong word and you are done for the semester.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--So many papers--Tough grader

comment: The articles were very relevant to reflect what your experiences are and what each person could learn and improve from. Great class, she is invested and really get gets to own her classes.
she's nice and hard at the same time!

I have never felt uncomfortable in a class until I took Professor Baskerville. She will shoot down your opinions without explanation and grades in a similar manner. Any attempt to discus your grade with her will result in her belittling you as a person.

This class has been really helpful to me. I really enjoyed the readings, which are very relevant to our future work in accounting and management. She cares about students and really passionate about teaching. She organized her class very logically so once you finished it, a whole picture comes together. Highly recommended
I enjoyed taking Professor Baskerville's class. She is friendly and helpful. Her class relies heavily on discussion of assigned case readings, so you do need to read them or you will not do well.

One of the fairest teachers I've ever had. Lays everything out for you at the beginning of the semester and tells you exactly what needs to be done to do well. Definitely not the easiest class I've ever taken but not out of the question to get a fairly easy A. She is always available to help students out and is very engaging in class. Great Teacher

Baskerville genuinely cares about her students, and she does a great job of engaging the whole class in discussion. We had no formal exams, just group projects and papers. The class was pretty easy as well, as long as you did the reading. Highly recommended!

Take this class! She is an incredibly nice, intelligent, and fair professor. Class is very enjoyable and she makes the subject interesting. Tests are a bit challenging, but if you study, you will be completely fine. She really wants students to learn and connects with every student. Do yourself a favor and take Baskerville - you will not regret it!

Best professor. It is really a great course - the most practical and helpful one I attended at Northeastern. I've learned a lot through tons of assignments and a closer-to-industry-level project. Jose is really nice and friendly and does want to help you when you are struggling with anything in web dev.

Best professor. He is so nice, I think the only thing that matters to him as students learn. He gives extensions if we are facing issues sometimes which makes us feel like he really wants us to learn.

I really like professor jose's teaching style, he explains everything very clear in lecture and always helpful when debugging student's code. although homework is a little bit time consuming but I learned a lot. definitely my favourite class so far.

One of the best classes in the MA program. Syllabus are organized, progression of topics is clear and naturally builds on what came before. You will learn a lot and have a project completed by the end. He is very clear and always willing to answer questions. Also very responsive to the class - gave multiple extensions when servers were down.
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Group projects--Clear grading criteria

comment: You can learn many technologies in this class. Jose is a great lecturer. He is not too strict with grading. He gives significant amount of assignments. You can use the project and assignments in this class in your portfolio.
Very helpful and caring professor. He records his lectures and posts them on his youtube channel. That way one can be a week ahead of class. Would highly recommend taking this class with him.
Hands down, one of the best professors at Northeastern University, Boston.
- "Spontaneous" final exam - Ignores piazza questions

Great professor! He is really good at coding, and sometimes he does the coding in class to help us understand the whys and hows. TBH his class is very intensive: quizzes, assignments, projects, exams... Though it makes the workload really heavy, the credit is dispensed to all these tasks as well so you are not doomed if you screw up one assignment.
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Accessible outside class--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: Everyone recommends prof Jose but honestly (&sadly) he is one of the worst profs I've had. AWOL on weekends, ambiguous assignments which take weeks to complete but you get just 1 week. Complained about this but got no relief! He gave 2 due during thanksgiving as well. He doesn't really teach you the important concepts, just glazes over a topic.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--LOTS OF HOMEWORK--BEWARE OF POP QUIZZES

comment: Super friendly and easily accessible outside class. You can text/call him and he is quick to respond. Assignments are along the lines of what is taught in class. You can get creative with the Project. He is not tough with grading, emphasizes more on learning basic web development concepts and building a website which adds value to your resume.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Amazing lectures

comment: Professor Jose is a great professor. He uses practical approach to teach the course. He writes code wherever required and explains the concept in full detail. He is very caring for his students. Always available. His passion for the subject is clearly visible in the way he teaches this course. Great assignments. Highly Recommended.
Great professor, great lectures.

Informative and inspirational lecture. Very comprehensive and friendly for the beginner. Hands on projects, one is simple by following the instruction given at each course, one is self-design by utilizing and applying the skills. 2 projects went on from the beginning of the semester in parallel. Then, you are ready for basic web development!
Best professor at Northeastern:)
Great lectures, great professor, very helpful and passionate. Gives great feedback and is the most accessible professor.
A real gem!

He is best at what he does, his lectures gives you deep insight into the logic behind the coding that is being done, he covers all the minute details that lay the foundation for being a learned Web Developer. Moreover, he is super responsive/active/agile is responding to queries on Piazza.   A BIG THUMBS UP to Prof. Jose.

Prof. Annunziato's Web Dev class is probably one of the best courses I have taken here at Northeastern. He seems really passionate about the technology and is effective in teaching it. Another plus side is his availability for office hours, and prompt response to posts on Piazza. Definitely recommend!

Really interesting seminar. Mark was very reasonable in the amount of work we must do for a capstone course. He gave some really interesting lectures and there was a good amount of student presentations. I liked the final project that was a grant proposal-type project. And he was nice enough to write me a letter of recommendation based on my work.

Mark is the perfect professor. Kind, intelligent, and inspiring. The seminar was a great prep for graduate school, and he was willing to write a letter of recommendation for me. The course mainly involved lots of reading and papers, but we also got to present a topic of our choice and we were exposed to writing a grant proposal as a final project.

Professor Prokosch was great. He made every day a joy to be in his class. I really learned so much that I feel is relatable to my life. Lectures were always interesting and there was always an opportunity to ask questions and to have some discussion. Exams and quizzes were straight from lecture. Study guides were super helpful. Awesome class!

Loved this guy. The course wall fully lecture-based, but those lectures were always entertaining and informative. All exams and quizzes were open-note and the study guides were really helpful. Great man, great course. Great elective.

I was a huge fan of Professor Prokosch. I enjoyed my time in class and thought the quizzes and exams were very reasonable. I would recommend his class to anyone. He was funny, engaging, and really nice.

I loved everything about this class. Mark always gave really interesting lectures with lots of supplemental videos and anecdotes. There was always some element of discussion and exams and quizzes were straightforward and always based on lectures rather than the textbook. Even though I took it fully remote, I always felt engaged and interested.

My favorite course at Northeastern. Professor Prokosch was great. He was funny and engaging. Never got bored during his lectures. There were three open-note quizzes and three exams. Study guides were very helpful. This elective led me to change my major to psychology!

There were lots of weekly readings and papers, but I guess that's expected in a capstone course. Through it all Mark made it really easy for me to want to do my best. His class actually gave me a platform to explore research interests that inspired me to look into a few master's programs. I highly recommend the seminar.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: To be honest, this is one of the most enjoyable and useful classes I have ever taken at Northeastern. Mark was an incredible professor. He has a voice of a professional narrator which never failed to keep my attention. The lectures were very engaging and the coursework was manageable. Recommended to all those taking Foundations of Psychology.
My favorite class of the semester and my favorite professor. 3 exams, 4 online quizzes, very interesting lectures. Professor Prokosch exceeded expectations.
Excellent professor. Excellent class. Highly recommend.

Professor Prokosch is an amazing professor. He can relate to who he is teaching and makes the content really interesting. We get to see a lot of real-world applications by watching case studies. We also can ask a lot of questions. He is really kind and passionate about psychology. 3 exams, 4 quizzes. Lectures are posted online.

HE IS THE BEST! Super helpful, very knowledgable, great communications skills, always available, it was a great pleasure to be in his class. I highly recommend taking Seminar course with Mark Prokosch!

Mark Prokosch is an amazing professor. He knows how to explain the material clearly and thoroughly while also making it extremely interesting. He has an amazing sense of humor and is overall just a really good guy. Highly recommend taking this class with him!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Respected--Get ready to read

comment: Professor Prokosch is extremely knowledgeable and supportive. He is quick in responding to e-mails, it was very important in times like these. He is a quick grader and provides the most in-depth descriptive feedback for each submitted work. Overall, he is the BEST!

Mark is the best. ever. I am so glad I took his course. He is very passionate about what he teaches, always willing to help/answer questions, and he tries to make class fun. Its very easy to motivate yourself to be in class when you can tell your professor wants to be there, too. Highly recommended.

Easily one of the best professors I've ever had, if you get the chance to take his class, please do. An incredibly kind, caring, and intelligent professor who gives amazing lectures. If you do the work and listen to lectures, the class is an easy A and you learn a lot of information. Cannot say enough good things about him!

Such an interesting class and a wonderful professor. Took it during covid so the exams and quizzes were all online and open-note so it was a pretty easy A. It was an elective course, but probably my favorite. Prokosch is great. Witty and engaging lectures even via Zoom.
Exams and quizzes were all open book!! Quizzes werent timed but exams were so be warned.

I really can't say enough good things about Professor Prokosch. I took the class over the summer and each class session was like 3 hours long, but class time went by relatively quickly because Prokosch is really entertaining when he lectures and there's a good amount of class discussion. I also felt like I learned a lot. Definitely recommend him.

This was honestly one of the best classes Ive taken in college, and Professor Prokosch is a huge reason why. I learned so much about not only psychology but myself as well. His lectures are very captivating and class goes by very quickly. Ill definitely be taking more psych classes in the future because of him. Highly recommend.

Professor Prokosch is the perfect college professor. He is extremely knowledgable and will answer any question outside of lecture material. Knows how to be funny (quirky humor) to engage his students. Extremely easy A so long as you know all information on the study guides - tests do not have any surprises. You will learn a lot too!

Super funny and such a nice guy. Lectures are interesting and he breaks them up with short videos that make them fly by. Only grades are a few online MC quizzes and MC tests, both are super easy if you follow his study guides. Attendance is not mandatory or needed and neither is the textbook.

This is my favorite class and favorite professor I have taken so far in college. Prokosch is a relly outstanding presenter. Super charismatic, smart, and fun. I really loved everything about this class and the lectures. Totally recommend him.

Mark is fantastic. I always found myself looking forward to coming to his class! There are 3 exams (2 midterm, 1 final) and none of them are cumulative. Quizzes are all online and open note. Very easy A if you take notes on the lectures and fill out the study guides he gives. Exams never stray from the study guide content.
YOU SHOULD TAKE THIS CLASS WITH MARK FOR SURE

Mark is a great professor who makes class engaging and exciting. Even though he does not take attendance, I find myself excited to go to his class. His tests are a bit dense, but extremely straightforward if you study your lecture notes. Also, do not buy the textbook. It was expensive and I did not open it once.

Amazing professor and an easy A guaranteed. It might seem like theres a lot of material but he gives a study guide for each exam, just study those and youll be fine. 25%*3 tests on lecture material + 25% online quizzes on textbook readings (quizlet has all the answers)

Prof. Prokosch was great. If you take the class over the summer, be prepared for long lectures, but he makes them super interesting and uses a lot of videos etc. Make sure to go to class, tests are worth 75% of the grade and the material is entirely covered in class. there is also a service-learning requirement of 6hrs (you take psych experiments)
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures--Caring

comment: He said he ran the class like a graduate course, which was intimating at first, but then I realized that it was geared towards preparing me for graduate school. We read a lot of articles across the field of social psych and had to do group presentations and write several papers. But Mark was a fair grader and gave good feedback. Highly recommend.

Professor Prokosch was wonderful and I truly enjoyed his class. The structure of lectures and the provided study guides were extremely accessible and helped me learn. Very smart guy. I appreciated his humor, his openness to questions, and his ability to make lectures both informative and engaging. I would happily take another class with him.

Professor Prokosch is amazing. He's certainly the best professor I've had so far (I'm in my fourth year). I really learned so much in his class. He's very helpful outside of class, and his lectures are super engaging. I switched my minor to psychology because of him.

Love him! He's funny and super nice! His lectures are not too heavy and break down lecture presentations w/ interesting short videos/docus. Some online quizzes that are open books which are easy. His tests are MC and very easy if you follow his study guide! Attendance not mandatory. Got a FBI guest speaker to come which was so cool! don't need book

Mark is an amazing professor. I have learned a lot about research in social psychology. He provides helpful feedback on papers and sets a comfortable atmosphere for learning. The seminar format allows for student-led learning rather than simply being lectured to, which has helped me to feel more confident in my presentation skills. He is top notch!

Mark is amazing. He was accessible outside of class, very caring, and absolutely hilarious. He tries to make the content as fun as possible. Assignments are based on almost weekly papers, which were sometimes very annoying, and class presentations. As long as you show up to class, put in effort into your papers, and do as he asks, you'll get an A.

He's great! He's very nice, makes dad jokes, makes a point to not cut students off even when someone's story goes on for a while. Pretty clear about what the tests were on, but they were online open note so while some questions were tricky, you could figure it out. The homework seems intimidating but it's simple and easy and fairly graded. 10/10
Prokosch is phenomenal.

Professor Prokosch is an excellent lecturer! Almost all of the things on his tests came from notes we took in class, so you don't really need to read the textbook, unless you want to clarify topics. He is funny and includes lots of videos in his lectures to make it interesting.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious--Amazing lectures

comment: Mark is a very nice guy and his lectures cover pretty much everything on the test. There really isn't any need to read the textbook as long as you read the power points. There are some questions on the test that are based on videos you can only view if you go to class. Overall, very approachable and nice guy whose lectures are interesting.

Professor Prokosch is one of my favorite teachers. He's a genuinely wonderful person, & he's a great teacher who is passionate about the subject. Always willing to offer help, answer questions in class, & understand when deadlines need to shift to accommodate that stressful week or two when tests/quizzes/etc are overwhelming. 10/10 recommend.
Man I loved this class. He's my most favorite professor I've had.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS--Amazing lectures

comment: Mark is a very chill professor, gives study guides for tests which are all multiple choice. Some questions are on videos discussed in lecture which are not posted to blackboard, but besides that it's an easy class.

I actually looked forward to going to class because the professor was such a great lecturer and an interesting guy. He posts his lecture slides online before each class, but you definitely need to go to class to do well on the tests.
The best intro course I have ever taken in any subject area. Professor Prokosch  is simply the best.
Makes an intro psych class interesting and personalized.

Attendence isn't mandatory, but if you don't want to read the book just go and take notes  because you won't need to get the book and he asks questions that come directly from the videos we watch in class. Honestly, just do not get the book and go to class, he even gives you study guides that you only really need the lecture slides to fill out

He's very friendly and interested in the topic, but he expects students to memorize EVERYTHING he says in lectures and makes no attempt to clarify which parts are the most important. Your entire grade is based on 3 tests that are extremely hard and the questions are very specific. It's almost impossible to get an A, but he's still a good teacher.
Not only he's a very passionate about the class, he's incredibly hilarious. He will definitely make you interested in psychology. Went into this class thinking I'll hate it but I absolutely loved it.
READ THE BOOK!

I appreciated his enthusiasm and that he included a lot of current topics in his lectures.  I would have preferred to have more than just 3 exams to base our grade on, but at least he was willing to give extra credit. He's the best professor I've had.

I had heard that I should take intro psych with Professor Prokosch.  I'm glad I did.  He is really interesting and I actually looked forward to his lectures. He also has a super dry sense of humor.  Also, one class he fell off a table - sort of on purpose - to help us remember what the hippocampus does. Highly recommend.
Prokosch is an awesome professor. Definitely need to come to class and take good notes.  I'm thinking about majoring in psychology thanks to him.

He is the best professor I have ever had in my 5 years at Northeastern. I'm about to graduate and his course really inspired me to pursue graduate school in psychology when I was initially unsure if it was for me.

The professor is great, but didn't really get to know him much because I didn't really get to interact with him. You come to a lecture, sit a lecture (pretty interesting), and do 3 exams within the semester. Hard to get an A though, really got to study--no make up tests.
Lectures were incredibly interesting, tests were confusingly worded. Hard to get an A since there are only three grades per semester.

He is a really good professor. His lectures are very clear and funny and though they are sometimes boring, the slideshows are all on blackboard and its easy to catch up. He gives study guides for every test. He also has the most adorable new baby that he talks about during his lectures about developmental psychology. Take this class!

My favorite class the semester I took it. His lectures are entertaining and easy to follow, and tests were all multiple choice and fairly easy as long as you studied. I only remember using the text book once though, so I'd suggest saving your money there. Otherwise, take this class!!!

He's a cool guy and a great teacher. His lectures are interesting, especially the videos. He explains the material well and with humor. He assigns reading from the textbook, but just focus on the lecture slides, and you'll do well.

He's pretty good. I like his lecture style. He explains concepts pretty clearly with (sometimes funny) examples. It's good that he posts the slides before class so that you can print them and bring them to class. He plays people's song requests and drinks cappuccino every class lol. Only thing I don't like about this class is that the MCQs exams.

i agree w/ the general consensus over his helpfulness and clarity; he is great.  HOWEVER, this is no regard an easy class! Test avgs (so far we've taken 3 of 4) are a 75 and he doesn't gives curves or extra credit. The 4 papers make up 20% and are all easy 100%.  Still, the grade of an avg student gets a C+/B-...not typical for a intro psych course

Posts slides. Classes are VERY interesting and easy to follow. Always funny and sometimes says anecdotes...Exams are all MCQs. Study the slides and your notes VERY well and you'll get an A. Focus on the videos he shows in class because he asks about them in his exams.

The best professor I've had by far. He makes everything so clear and he is also hilarious. His slides are all up on blackboard but attend class to watch the videos as they will show up on exams. I would take another class with him in a heartbeat. He is the best!!!!

Great at teaching. As clear as can be dealing with a lot of information to cover in a relatively short amount of time. Easy to understand said information. Attendance to class almost paramount to getting good grades as he does a better job than the textbooks explaining.

Dr. Ho is great, he cares about his students and facilitates an open and comfortable learning environment. You can tell he is really passionate about the subject matter and very much an expert. You should get ready to do a good amount of homework if you're planning on taking this class, but it's not anything that won't benefit you in the long run!

Hubert is a beast. 10/10 music professor, he really makes the NU music program worth it. I did a few of his classes. He's highly skilled as a musician and he's pretty good at explaining things if you ask questions. The work is not usually very easy but it is never a lot so you get to explore things well. And he is funny and very aware.

Very fun professor, a bit silly. Tries really hard to make sure you understand the material, and he will call on every person in class so if you're shy be prepared. A reasonable amount of homework that you don't automatically get an A on but if you keep up you'll be fine. Lots of group discussion
Such an awful professor. Inconsiderate, so much work. This class literally made me break down 3 times a week. Avoid, especially if you run anxious. He has good intentions, but NOT a good experience.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: As someone who's never taken a music theory course before, I found his class to be one of the hardest things I've ever taken. He moves really, really fast in the class, so it was difficult for me to catch up. Seems like a good person, but i wouldn't take a course from him unless i was an experienced musician.

Professor Ho is really humorous, and he always made the class interesting by playing us some songs to explain the music theory. He knows everyone's names because he gets everyone engaged in class. There are a lot of quizzes but very easy as long as you understand the theory. One of my favorite class at Northeastern! Recommended!
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Clear grading criteria

comment: DO NOT TAKE FILM MUSIC! This may seem like an easy A elective, but it is anything but. Even though this class is for non-majors, he takes this class way too seriously. There are so many assignments and readings every week, and you need to watch at least one movie a week. He is disorganized and unclear and grades the essays too harshly.
Ho is an experience. He's very nice and kind of bizarre. I had a faint feeling of anxiety whenever I was in his class, but it's better than being bored. I would recommend.

DO NOT TAKE THIS CLASS!!! I cannot stress enough how bad it was. The professor is not bad, but the content is impossible for an 1100 class. If you are not a music major STAY AWAY. Taking this class was probably my worst mistake in Northeastern

Very charismatic professor with a corny sense of humor. He teaches at a very fast pace, but slows down if students ask and seems to be learning to ask students if he needs to slow down. Weekly quizzes, and nightly homeworks, with a final project and two exams. He's probably the most likely teacher to really get you excited about music theory.

Having Professor Ho for Film Music has been a nightmare. The timeline for assignments in class is so messed up that you never end up completing them all. He assigns group papers with a short page limit, so you cannot add enough info to get a good grade. He also expects you to write critical analyses WHILE using other sources.... Stay away.

Professor ho is a brilliant professor, very skilled in music. hes a little unclear sometimes and expects you to know dates from the syllabus without him explicitly saying so. class was pretty easy and straightforward

I've had professor Ho for 3 different classes now, and I'll be taking a 4th with him in the Fall. He is a brilliant mind, a hilarious (but corny) guy, and is always willing to help students in need. He moves very quickly but will slow down when asked. Some people won't like how upfront he is, but honestly, this man is a genius, take his classes.

Hubert Ho has changed the way I see music, arrange my furniture and talk to my friends and family. He is ridiculous. Did I mention he has perfect pitch? Honestly, Hubert is a great guy, with a sense of humor and a firm understanding of his field. Class flies by (my first time check is usually half way through class) and Hubert makes it interesting.

Great professor, really goes in depth individually correcting your capstone drafts so you know exactly what you need to do to get a 100. Keeps things light - makes a lot of jokes and plays a lot of videos but also seriously knows what he's talking about. Majored in physics/music at harvard so yeah, smart guy

Hubert is not afraid to act silly in front of the class in order to get his point across. He actually cares about students and always answered the few questions I had completely. I really enjoyed his class and learned aspects of film that I'll never forget. I think he's a great teacher overall and the class was easy.

He's a nice guy. He explains things pretty well and the mid-term and final aren't so bad if you follow his powerpoints and pay attention in class. He's not afraid to sound a little dorky when he starts humming out different tunes, and I'm glad he does because it really helps you understand exactly what he's talking about. Recommended.

Prof Seo is the best. I started this course VERY overwhelmed, but her lectures are clear, and her office hours were very useful. She cares a lot and will try very hard to make sure you understand the material. She can notice when students get stressed and cracks jokes to relieve the pressure. Oh, and her notes are beautiful!
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Hilarious--Amazing lectures

comment: She's a super queen
Prof Seo is a great teacher. She is invested in teaching her students. Her examples in class are very clear and she gives good study material for exams.

Sumi is great prof and makes things very easy with good quiz and test reviews. While she does a good job covering everything, she goes very very fast oftentimes and a lot of the work needed to succeed is from outside studying. Overall, Sumi is great for Calc 3 since its arguably the strangest math in the calc series
ratingTags: Accessible outside class--Skip class? You won't pass.--Test heavy

comment: Professor Seo is a great mathematics professor. She outlines things very well and teaches you exactly what you need to know to grasp the concept. I had her for Calc 3 and will have her again for Linear Algebra in the Fall. Definitely try and take your math classes with her! Will be worth it.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Skip class? You won't pass.--Amazing lectures

comment: Amazing professor! Lectures are always clear and she lets you know what you need to know for tests! If you do the homework, you're almost guaranteed an A.

Sumi isn't necessarily a bad teacher. She knows her material and is very adept at teaching it. Yet, the classes she teaches are difficult and the pace at which she moves is extremely quick. At most times, it's hard to keep up and while she encourages students to ask questions, she doesn't give them enough time to think about it.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--Test heavy

comment: Sumi Seo is AMAZING! She is a very nice lady and knows how to keep the lectures interesting. Highly recommend for any math class.
She's the truth

Professor Seo is the best math professor I've had at Northeastern University. Her lectures do a great job of explaining hard to understand math concepts and she does many examples to make sure her students comprehend the material. Class does require some out of class studying to do well on quizzes and tests but is an easy A otherwise.

This is the second class I've had Seo for and I like her a lot. She is usually very clear about what she wants you to know and what you will be graded on. She goes pretty fast, so if you don't have time to go to extra help or learn by working through things, this may not be for you. But I still regard as a very solid choice. Responds to emails well
ratingTags: Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Sumi is a caring and friendly person. She is always willing to help.

Fantastic professor. I had her for Calc 3 and her lectures were amazing. She's willing to answer any questions, or meet outside of class. Grading was based only on quizzes, the two exams, and the final, so you have to stay on top of the material. Easiest way to do that is by showing up. She keeps lectures interesting and leaves time to take notes.
