She talks a mile a minute, and every second is relevant to the topic. She gives an outline of the topic on a powerpoint, but there is so much more she talks about, and it pops up on the exams. She doesn't care for memorization; rather, she cares for how you apply the concept. She uses Tegrity which is super helpful.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Took this class even though I had AP Bio credit. It was way harder than expected but she is a really good lecturer. She never stutters and goes over everything in such detail. The way to pass is to memorize literally everything she says. Good luck
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--TEST HEAVY--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Hated this class, tests are super hard and questions are unclear. Don't take if you don't have to.

Dr. Potts-Santone was a good professor. She lectures intensely but puts up recordings on Tegrity.  She grades fairly but only 3 exams in the class(plus few other assignments). She isn't too approachable but emails quickly. Recommend the class if you like the material and are good at memorizing large chunks of information.

The tests are pretty tough and very detailed, there is a lot of memorization required. She gives you chances to get points during the semester with online quizzes and random bonus points for coming to class (usually 3 per exam). Posts recorded lectures online which is VERY helpful because she talks too much and too fast during lecture.
Had her for Human Parasitology - tests are super intense, lots of memorization, super detailed PPTs, but she's a nice professor
Avoid her at all costs. She actually made me hate Biology.

Go to class. She posts her lectures online but its helpful to go to class because 1. You can get the information twice that way and 2. she gives bonus points randomly throughout the semester. Her tests are very tricky even though she says she doesn't want to trick you, so study often. Her class is hard but worth it.

She isn't really that bad. She uploads a recording of all her lectures with the powerpoints online which is extremely helpful if you don't feel like going to class at 8am or if you want to brush up before a test. She also gives extra credit questions if you go to class. Her tests are fine if you actually study.

If you ever have to take her class, good luck guys cause you will need it. Her tests are really tough and you really have to know the topics really well because she is really specific with her questions. Her multiple choice questions are really hard and the answer is really hard to find because the answers are really close to each other.
Awful Presenter. Just goes through powerpoints with clusters of information which is organized terribly. A lot of random facts about parasites thrown in the middle.

I used to like Biology before I joined this class. While she is clear in her manner of speaking her tests so far have been hard. She posts all of the lectures on Tegrity. Class is very boring and monotone and she does not stop talking for 60 minutes straight. Her tests are not easy. You can't just know the material and pass the test. Dont take her.

She is a good teacher and can present a lot of information clearly. However, she presents a ton of info. I took Gen. Bio and it probably should have been MicroBio. She spends a lot of time on specific details that are not all necessarily on the test.

I really loved the class and she was great at teaching it but theres a ton of information to learn so you need to start studying early for the exams! Two tests, cumulative final, and some assignments throughout the semester. Book was helpful but not totally necessary and definitely go to class.

Great prof, crystal clear directions and assignments, gives extra credit! Has office hours, go to them! The tests really aren't so bad, you just HAVE to attend class (not everything is in the tegrity) and read the textbook! As long as one puts medium effort, you should do fine. The lectures are extremely helpful. She knew me by name out of 150 kids

Oh, Potts. Very likable as a professor but as far as teaching style, it's straight reading off of the (quite pretty) lecture slides. Her study guides give you a pretty good idea of what will be on the test, but bet your butt that she will throw in tangent things that you would not be able to locate in the lecture notes. Study hard, kids.

She's a nice person but she doesn't hand out grades for free. She requires you to know every specific detail she covered, and her tests are full of trick questions. That being said, she does give bonus points for showing up to class.

Honestly avoid Potts-Santone at all costs. She is a robot. She reads off the slides and thats that. Her tests are 60 multiple choice you have an hour and not a second longer. Good Luck! For some reason its not good enough to know the material you have to be able to figure out her trick questions and riddles too! This class is made to weed kids out.

Dr. Potts Santone was absolutely one of the best, most organized and inspiring teachers I've ever had.  It's clear she puts time and thought into preparing her lectures- she made the material  accessible and fascinating.  I looked forward to going to class!  Tests and scope of material covered are difficult but fair- be ready to study!

Talks really fast during lecture, but records and posts every class via tegrity. DO NOT RELY ON TEGRITY! She gives extra credit sometimes to those who show up to her class on a given day because so many people make the mistake of relying on tegrity and those are typically the ones who don't do well. Her tests are tough,  but shes very approachable.
Her tests are really vague. You are expected to know every tiny detail about everything. Be prepared to work

Prepare to have slides with barely any information on them and then writing 2 paragraphs worth of information and terms in lecture that she doesn't put anywhere (including the textbook). When material becomes a little more difficult for some reason she becomes extremely disorganized. Notes are unreliable and the textbook is unreliable. Good luck
Use Tegrity

She really knows her stuff and is really excited to share that material with you. At first, I was angry w/ all the material we had to learn for 1 exam, then I woke up and realized that I am in college = Hard Work.  Test questions are like riddles, wrapped in enigmas- they are not direct at all. That being said, really know all material. Use Tegrity

Hands down the worst teacher I have ever had. Her tests are not clear at all. She does not scale even when the test averages are are in the 60's. She doesnt care about her students at all and makes it seem like she likes to see you struggle. I would not recommend her to anyone.

Very clear and helpful professor. Posts all of her lectures on tegrity so it's not that harmful if you don't go to class. Tests are straight from lectures and some references to the textbook. Overall, challenging but fair class. You get a good grade if you put in effort

Keeps the lectures interesting. Sometimes she only has 8 AM classes, but she posts everything on Tegrity, unless it's not working. Tests are VERY wordy. 63 extremely wordy MCQs in less than an hour. Fair distribution of grades. 25% goes to lab (which is easy in BIO2)

She's a very smart, clear teacher who doesn't just give away As - her exams are tricky, you have to really understand the material.  That being said, if you do the work you'll do well.  I love her lectures.

I had her a few years ago (pharmacy), and looking back on old tests, they were terribly fair. Anyone who wants to succeed as a pharmacy major will get used to this type of test, or fail. It can be a bit of a transition, but She is a lot better than what's coming- she speaks clear English, uses a good textbook, and reviews everythi
Her tests are very wordy and hard to think through. You have to study. BUt her Tegrity classes online are useful. Overall she was okay.

Tests are very confusing and you have to figure out what the question is asking before you can answer. You can tell she doesn't write her own test and probably uses a test generator. You have to really work hard which can be difficult with a heavy course load.

Her tests are very wordy and confusing. The material itself is not that hard, but the test itself is like a riddle that you have to solve to figure out what each question is actually asking. Each answer also has multiple parts to try and trip you up. Lecture is very fast paced and it is easy to fall back. Plan on using the textbook a lot!
Tests are very hard. Questions are very wordy and hard to understand. Study for the next test 2-3 days after the previous test. Use office hours and e-mail.

She is a really great instructor and knows her stuff.  Study early Sometimes she goes off on tangents and it becomes hard to distinguish what information is important.  You do not need to attend class, TEGRITY = AMAZING.  She is really nice and readily available for help and is always timely with email responses even on weekends.  HIGHLY RECOMMEND!
i went to class all first semester and got a c- in bio 1, went to class maybe 3 times 2nd semester, got a b- in bio 2. you dont need to go to class, but study for the tests use tegrity and the book.

had for both Gen Bio 1 & Gen Bio 2...at first the class size, information and her expectations might overwhelm you but I learned so much from taking this class. The book helps to reinforce her lectures but Bio 2 was more about the lectures. Her tests are tricky but after awhile you learn to distinguish what she chooses to put on tests.

She's a really nice lady and helpful if you go to her and ask questions. she does a lot for her students and grades the tests within a few hours sometimes. Her tests are really hard esp in BIOL2 but if you study a lot you can still get a good grade because she helps a lot by dropping and averaging lowest tests and quiz grades

Had her for general bio 1 and 2. You need to put a lot of effort into this class, but its worth it, and you will learn a lot. Very knowledgeable.  I would print out a copy of the powerpoint slides and take notes on them while rewatching the lectures on tegrity on blackboard.  After that is done, skim the book. A lot of work, but it will pay off.

Had her for BIO 1 and 2. Prof is super knowledgeable... Lectures can sound repeated and boring sometimes. Tests are very wordy- come prepared! Use textbook, studyguides, online book website flashcards to help study... Lots of effort = good grade.
Her tests are very confusing. she gives out quizzes and she does not curve grades. Very strict.

ok, honestly i had her for both bio 1 and 2 and all i can say is the more often i skipped class the better I did, find a way to study that works, and use it, she has no mercy for you if you forget anything.

Invert. Zoology is very hard. Very exacting and strict grading, no curve. Half the test is take-home, so it's easy to get a passable grade, but the in  class portion is very hard. Very nice and friendly. There is a LOT of material in the class; even at a seeming breakneck pace, we were still behind. Hope you know some Latin; vast amt of terminology

The only thing that is a drag is the 8am time slot.  but she is very clear and knowledgeable about biology!  its definitely possible to get an A, just take the time to really study.  It's college, it's obv not going to be easy but you will learn a lot!
amazing teacher. she kept the topic interesting at all times. you must attend class if you would like to do well, but she made everything interesting
very hard class, lots of information.  Seems very mean and cold in beginning, but if you go see her in office hours shes a really kind woman. dont miss class.
very hard

pretty good teacher even though lectures are extremely boring. be prepared for a rough semester if you have her at 8am, not the most pleasant thing to wake up to. her tests are very hard, and need a good few days of studying for a decent grade.

A great teacher, very enthusiastic and easy to understand. Make sure you go to class, take detailed notes, read the textbook, study the labs and you should be fine. Pretty easy A and really enjoyable! Only negative was the 8am shocker

She is a good teacher who wants you to do good. The class is hard and she might come off as mean, You just need to put the time into it. You have to study, my advise is to study right from the class powerpoints and notes, and at the end read throught he book for any extra information, or to get a better understanding of the material.

STUDY HARD, READ THE BOOK, GET FRIENDS IN CLASS, LAB DEF HELPS!! Second semester practicals are a pain but could def help your grade. She's a pretty nice person it's just that she gives WAYYY too much information. Class was pointless to me but useful to others. Either read the book word for word or go to class to do well.

I struggled bigggg time last semester at the beginning. She's really nice once you go see her, and show her you care about your grades. I did horrible on the first two exams and still passed with a B. Go to class to get your attendance points (they help!). And study hardddddd because her tests cover everythingggg. She's tough, but ey work with her!
Gen Bio 1 &2 were my hardest classes. Hard/ very tricky tests. Unfriendly. Thinks everyone should care about bio..but we don't.
She's not very nice, but she's helpful and clear.  As long as you pay attention, you will get an A
love the class, and good teacher. Can be friendly if you give her respect but I've heard she can be not so helpful if your rude.
tricky tests. annoying voice. if youve taken AP bio, you can cake through the course
test are so hard...just give up guys!!

My least favorite class for this year. She is a nice person, but her exams are extremely hard, especially for bio 2. Memorize(I mean literally from a to z.) the book will help you out(if you can of course. A LOT of material in a SHORT period of time. For me, I've read the book 3 times and still couldn't do well.
attendance is not mandatory. her test is really hard and you might wanna change your professor. she ruined my freshman year
i really really really dont like this class.  There is a lot of material and questions on tests are often impossibly specific.  If you have a strong background in Bio, you'll be ok.
not a very nice teacher. actually was my least liked teacher freshman year. tests were very difficult. make sure to go to class and pay attention AND read the book.
Seems like a nice woman; pretty attractive too :)

Definitely a lot of material in a short time. Attendance isn't mandatory especially if you're just gonna sleep in class--you get notes some other way. Tests are very specific but not impossible. Reading the book and studying are musts. She's overall fair, it's just SO much material, overwhelming too. Doing well in lab should help boost your grade

Anal about cheating, seems very crabby and ****y, but is easy to do well in her class. show up to lecture if you feel like it, she only takes attendance when most people don't show up and it's not worth much. read the textbook well because she asks very specific questions.

a lot of material in a short time- made exams somewhat difficult. you pretty much have to know your stuff. not sure about clarity- fell asleep half the time in lectures and only stayed awake to take notes =T good thing she puts the ppts online.

WWould not recommend if not required. Material is interesting but there is ALOT of it.  Exam questions are not straight forward.  Slightly intimidating professor but nice in person.  Attendance in lecture is not mandatory but you will not do well if do not go. Class averages were in low 70s, hard class but not impossible.

Overall a great professor.  She seems like she would not be helpful but, if you go and talk to her she is a sweet, very helpful woman.  The tests are difficult but an A is possible with moderate studying. DO NOT leave studying for the night before!

must go to class AND read the book. When she finishes a chapter in class, start studying it. People who don't do well in her class don't study correctly and leave it to last minute. I started studying so early for tests and got A's.Shes not impossible but tough.Listening to her gets tedious

she is a nice person, but she likes to hear herself talk. she genuinely cares about you passing though so if you go to the lectures, take notes, and study in advance you'll be fine. if you don't go to class and only study the night before the test don't expect to get higher than a C. nice woman though and she is fair.
hard but not impossible ... second semester (Bio 2) much easier if you like anatomy, even though you will probably never need to remember it if you are a pharmacy major.
bio 2 is nothing like bio 1.  labs much harder.  reading textbook is helpful.  moderately hard class...but lowest test score and quiz is dropped.  class averages around 73.

The easiest way to learn in this class is to outline the text, memorize terms, and take the quizzes provided by the text's website. Don't bother showing up for class except to get answers to online quizzes. Also, don't blow off the quizzes or the first test--you may find yourself in trouble later on. An easy B but a hard A.
Wants students to learn.  Fair grader- all tests and quizzes are multiple choice.  Although attendance is not mandatory, she will occasionally give bonus points for going to class

I thought she had a kind of annoying personality and she talked wicked fast. Other than that however, she explained everything very clearly, and the class was so fast paced that you didn't have a chance to get too bored if you were at all interested in biology. Tests/quizzes were very wordy but all multiple choice. Pretty good,Ide take her again.

Class is a waste. Just use the textbook, study it like crazy, and use the book website. All you need is the book to do well,  but it's still a hard class. You definitely need to put time into it and actually read and study on a regular basis.

She talks way too fast that I stopped taking notes after awhile because my hand kept cramping up and I wasn't comprehending anything she was saying.  I got the same grade on all 3 tests and stopped going to class after the first one.  You absolutely need the book..many test questions are from the book, and most questions are on the little details.

The class is fast paced - she gives a lot of notes.  It's really hard to get an A but not that hard to get a B+ - one of those type of classes.  She can seem unapproachable, but if you seem interested in one of her topics, she will chat with you and help you out.

Good teacher, yet a very difficult class. She talks very fast, and the questions on the exams can be tricky because you really need to throughly understand the material. She can be a bit hard to communicate with at times, but overall is a nice woman that you can tell really knows what she is teaching.

She talks wayyyyy too fast. I got the same grade on the first test that i did on the second but I didn't go to any of the classes for the second one. The class is very BORING, not to mention it's at 8 am     She can be rude to students at times.
Her enthusiasm is contagious.

She is a great teacher and explains everything u will need to know. u def need to read the book for the exams because either you wont go to class and wont have the notes or the notes you took you wont understand.  Lab is an easy A, but the quizes and tests are not.  The tests are pretty hard but if you study for them you should be able to get a B.

This was my 2nd semester in her class, and this time it was much worse. the tests were too difficult, she spoke too quickly and half the test came from the book, not the notes in class. if she slowed down, the class would be boring, but do-able.

I had her for Bio 1 and 2.  Bio 1 was fine, lots of reading and studying but it was relatively easy to do well.  Bio 2 is a different story.  There is so much information that is really unneccesary, considering half the class are Pharmacy majors and don't need to learn about starfish.  She is very helpful and wants students to do well.  Lab= death.
Talks very fast in lecture and can get a little boring, but she is very helpful at office hours and makes herself very available.

Very easy to understand. Can talk a bit too quickly, but everything she talks about in lecture is in the book unless she specifies otherwise. Great professor, just look over your lecture notes, read the book, and you'll do great on the tests!

A Professional Professor. respectful and knows her stuff. Shes ready to answer any question...and shows that shes concerned about her students. Willing to sacrifice alot to make things easier. Bonds well w/ others. Slight problem is that she sounds like a book.very interesting but she always teaches morning classes, so u cant help but sleep. +Sweet
okay teacher...spend the time reading the material beforehand and you'll do fine.

She is a very nice woman who I enjoyed learning from. She loves teaching and wants you to understand the material. She has a reputation for being very hard but that is because you actually have to keep up with the reading and review in order to do well. Overall she is a great professor.
great

Good teacher, she talks about a lot at once, but she'll draw a lot on the overhead so that it makes sense. Talks too fast, but she can go to class and she'll teach, don't always have to teach yourself before class, and thats good. :)

she's kind of annoying, all she does is go with the book and uses her own terms for certain things.  Your better off reading the text a few times than going to the class.  Just make sure you know when online quizzes are.
I reccommend reading the material a few times. If you do that, you'll get an A.

nice woman, knows a lot of information and wants you to know it too.  tests are moderately difficult because they require thinking (like college tests should).  study using the chapter quizzes, online quizzes from the book, and her quizzes and you'll do fine.  keep up with the reading and spend youre extra time reviewing and you'll do fine.
Very hard class, but she is a good teacher, Any Bio class will have a lot of material. She is strict but will help you to understand.

It was a diffucult class. Bio 1 was alot easier. In Bio 2 she read straight from the book. If you know all the study guide it isnt good enough. You have to be able to understand her questions and if you can you will be fine.

Past raters are likely people that didn't do well in this class.She is not interesting,but bc the material isn't interesting.Just keep up with the reading, take the quizzes at the end of each chapter and you get an A.Those that struggle don't deserve to be in college and I'm embarrassed for them.
haaarrrrddd
Her explanations are a little unclear and she covers a lot of material in a short time. I took the quizzes on the cd that came with the book and that helped me prepare for tests.

Potts-Santone is crazy.  I was very interested in biology before her class.  Now, I'm not interested in taking another class with her.  If you don't go to lecture, you WILL have a hard time with tests, since the tests use lots of in-class, VERY specific, references.  She is boring and uninteresting.

Her class covers alot of material, but her tests aren't ridiculously hard as long as you put some time in to study. Her lectures are almost word for word of out the chapter outlines which can be found on the website. Bring these to class and just add any extra info. Study these and you're all set!
She knows her stuff like no one else, and loves teaching it.  Very nice and willing to do all she can to help students.  One of my favorite professors thus far.
Very clear on what she expects of you, but the tests are so specific and difficult.  Try to wake up for the 8 AM classes or you'll be lost.
crams a lotta stuff in one test & is extremely specific as to what she test you on...she sucks. i cant wait to get out of her class! ps u will be napping in her lectures

Her classes are very intensive. She expects a lot. Her method of lecture is a little boring at times and the tests cover lots of material. However she is more than willing to give extra help to anyone who wants it. Be prepared for a lot of reading.

If a teacher can't put a proper sentance together, she shouldn't be teaching.  Feels like she reads the chapter right before class, then explains it in great detail, confusing everyone, and then tests students on specific details of other information. run
tests are very hard.
This class is soo hard.  She goes in so much detail, and is hard to keep up with.  But usually she teaches right out of the book
Hardiest teacher i think i will ever encounter.  The exams are so specific.  Talks a mile a minute and goes through 5 chapters a class.  Have Fun!
Gives alot of notes in each class but pretty much goes by the book. Gives a study guide for every exam and drops the lowest score. Nice lady who just wants you to learn.
lots of notes and material covered, but it is presented in a way that is easy to understand.
wicked hot!
She gives a lot of notes...take them, study them,study them again and you will do fine
No Comments
No Comments
She just throws driagrams up on the board and writes random words all over them and then says that there are no diagrams on the tests

She might be hard but she is really understanding and helpful. I wouldn't want another anatomy professor - well unless there was one that just handed out A's. She is probably the best prof. I have had here.
No Comments
No Comments
Chris is a very chill and laid back professor. All the fundamental concepts are very clearly taught because the text book in itself is easy to follow. The TA's are so kind and helpful.
Prof amato is extremely chill and understanding and understands students problems. He is a great professor and TAs are amazing.
Good course to learn the basics of AI.
ratingTags: Graded by few things--Test heavy--Group projects

comment: literally do not bother going to class. do yourself a favor and watch the online berkeley lectures, they are 1000% the same material and are explained infinitely more clearly.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--LOTS OF HOMEWORK

comment: The worst teacher I have ever had. Awful teaching method. Terrible grading approach. My friends at previous university of this professor (North Carolina State Uni) also had very bad experiences with her. The main reason why this professor came to Northeastern University was that there were so many complaints against her at the previous university.

Her class is awful. she is not recommended at all. Homework takes forever and is very hard, long and kind of useless. The textbook is totally vague and confusing!! Despite all of these, the grading is a disaster!!!
Tough professor, with no flexibility at all.

I came into the class with virtually no knowledge or background of academic philosophy or political theory at all. The readings were intimidating, daunting, and challenging, but Professor Lustila did a stellar job of making the content funny, understandable, and relatable to the human experience. He is also incredibly kind and understanding.

Getty is a great teacher. He's very good at talking about the philosophical material in ways that are understandable and even relatable, and the class meetings were entertaining. To his credit, it seems like he's always able to develop a good classroom community. In terms of work there's a lot of reading, which can suck, but that's how it goes.

Getty is a lad. Incredible lecturer who will change the way you think. Take him if you can. Also a very soft grader; just read the sparknotes before class and you're set. I was never overwhelmed with work in his class but still learned a ton. Can't ask for more than that
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Get ready to read--Amazing lectures

comment: If you have a chance to take a class with Prof. Lustila, I would jump at the chance. Whether you are phil or stem, he is great at facilitating discussions and helping everyone out with their understanding of the material or their papers. Funny and succinct analysis of wide ranging or confusing theory. Great guy, always willing to help outside class

Prof Lustila is the best I've had at Northeastern. As I am new to philosophy, Getty made the subject easier to understand and was eager to explain anything we didn't get the first time. He's accessible, and genuinely cares about not only the subject matter but every one of his students. He gives excellent feedback on essays and is a lovely person.

Getty is the best. He made this class so much fun while still teaching the material very well. He created an environment where I felt comfortable working through tough questions with my classmates, and his attitude was really conducive to a great learning environment. I can't stress enough how great this guy is.

This class was great! Professor Lustila was really nice and made ethics interesting to learn about. His goal was to get us to understand the content and philosophy and teach us how to write in it, and he never felt judgemental. Would definitely take this class again.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--So many papers

comment: She hardly ever had instructions for the assignments in canvas, so if you weren't in the class when she randomly explained it (with very little detail, and not recorded) you didn't know what the assignment was. Poor understanding and use of canvas. None of her lectures were more than a retelling of the textbook or a video she just showed.
A fair grader.

Her lectures were boring, and the tests were heavily textbook based. She does curve exams which is a plus. However, she is quite rude to students and insensitive. I was excited for this class as well due to her high ratings.

Maybe she is a different type of professor in person. But online, her lectures were boring. She forces our cameras to be on and mentions she will screenshot to check back later. She is quite rude if you answer wrong or have differing opinions than hers. She is also insensitive to different cultures considering she teaches an international class.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Lecture heavy--So many papers

comment: I hated this class. Boring, useless lectures. Textbook-heavy proctored tests. She's rude and dismissive, enjoys laughing at students when they answer something incorrectly. Video needs to be on for the entirety of class for participation, takes note if you turn it off. Likes randomly taking photos of the class to later check if you were focusing

Professor Un's lectures aren't super interesting but she does try to keep students engaged! She's a very nice professor who is very fun to talk to after class. Her exams are heavily textbook & case study based; she does give generous curves on her exams. She's also a lenient grader.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: extremely intelligent professor who puts a lot of effort into engaging students in class. She responds well to class participation as she enjoys discussion about the day's current events. Very caring and funny

She is very intelligent and responds very well to participation and questions. The class is one where you have constant work and have to be on top of your game, but Professor Un makes the work enjoyable and relevant. She begins each class with discussion about the news which was a good way to ease the class in. Great professor!

Annique's lectures are boring; her exam 2 and exam 3 are easy. Exam 1 is a bit tough but as long as you read the textbook, you will do well. She grades debate, participation, and group projects very easily. If you put work in, you will get at least an A-. She gives extra credit as well. Overall, this class is an easy A for me.

Professor Un is super nice and really cares about your students. She wants her students to do well in the class and is willing to meet with you outside of class for extra support. If you put in the work, you should be able to get at least an A- if not better. Multiple choice exams are pretty tough but they are curved.

Fine class, nothing crazy. There is almost no work throughout the semester and then quickly ramps up to almost unmanageable levels towards the end. Easy exams, but I still learned some international business. Definitely a good choice if you want a chill class with an easy A. Also, she constantly giggles at her own jokes which is pretty entertaining

Waste of my time. Made me dislike international business. Extremely boring lectures nearly every day. Exams are all multiple choice based on the textbook, often with repeats or multiple questions on the same topic in a row. & most of the time they will have nothing to do with whats talked about in class. Huge curves (16+ points).

Prof. Un is nice and the class is very average. She makes the material easy and is a lenient grader. She likes to check in with groups to see their progress on papers which was helpful to know what she wanted and had reviews before exams. Most of the reading is super boring and unnecessary she has you do a lot of case studies. Overall easy grade.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--GROUP PROJECTS

comment: A very nice kind professor who really cared about her students. Excellent teaching styles, using different approaches to ensure everyone understood the materials.
ratingTags: Participation matters--Skip class? You won't pass.--ACCESSIBLE OUTSIDE CLASS

comment: Amazing teacher who made hard topics easy to understand by using industry and international experiences to show how things really work in other countries.
Excellent prof who cares about everyone!

I agree with the previous posters about her having favorites. The class itself was not too difficult; it was heavy on reading and group projects but the exams were straightforward. Participation matters!

She means well, but this woman cannot teach for the life of her. She picks favorites (if you're not international, she is disinterested) and goes on the most wild tangents about her job and how much she travels. Class was very hard to sit through as there was always a very awkward tension.

Professor Un is nice and approachable. Your grade is based alot on the group projects that you do so If you get a bad group then you might have a tough time. However, the assignments and exams are not that hard and it isn't too hard to get an A on them.

This class was super easy. Tests aren't worth very much of the final grade and is mostly made up of a bunch of group work and presentations. I somehow ended up wth an A- even though i had gotten high A's in every single assignment and project.. weird... besides that this class is easy. Prof Un is super nice too.
Lectures are Long and Boring There are only 2 tests a semester You need to have a good and well prepared group to do well (Hint: make PowerPoints for every presentation, even if it is a debate)

Professor Un is extremely nice, helpful, and informative. Her extensive experience in international business helps us connect the material to the real world. The group projects are the worst. She assigns groups alphabetically, don't be surprised if you end up with a useless group. Tests are easy. Final paper is 10 pages MAX, she tells you this late
Cool professor! Debates in her class are awesome! Apply business concepts to real world cases, like why Walmart failed in Germany, South Korea? Really get you thinking.
She's really funny! Brings stuff from other countries to explain how companies do business in other countries!
Best prof ever! Her ARAMCO case was amazing. Changed my life. I don't think she ever taught MGSC2301. Is MGSC2301 a real class?
Worst teacher in the history of colleges.
Fantastic professor!
Trade within Africa was interesting!
loved this professor! Learned a lot!

Avoid her. Terrible teacher and ended up being a ridiculously hard and unfair grader. Goes on tangents about irrelevant topics. Chooses 2 or 3 favorites and makes it known she's disinterested in everyone else.

Nice lady but cannot teach effectively. Focuses far too much on Asian countries in attempting to tie in course content with reality. That being said, incorporate Asia into your papers or group project and you'll get an A. Didn't learn much form this course and that's a shame given International Business is a topic of growing importance for managers
I did too. Awesome class!
I did well in her class!
She is a nice person but seriously, one of the worst teacher I had.
She can bridge the cultural differences in Europe and Asia because of her experiences in many Asian and European countries. I agree with all the positive comments provided.

This is the only professor who would go out of her way to help students prepare for the exams by giving a practice exam before each exam. If this is not nice, I don't know what is. I did less well on EXAM 2, but it was a fair exam.
Professor Un has been posting all of our scores on BB and still constantly reminds us that her door is always open to talk about any thing we want. I visited her recently and found to be true.

I am enjoying professor Un's class immensely. She makes extra effort in helping international students adjust to the American business academic environment. The textbook we use has many Japanese examples. Since she has a lot of experiences in Japan, she elaborates on these examples using her own professional experiences there.

This is one of the worst teacher I have ever had. She interrupts the students all the time which is very frustrating, she has an obsession with Japan Everything is related to Japan. This is the most boring class I took, and she did not make it fun to learn at all
This is the best class I ever had at NU. I never thought I could learn so much about the world in just a few months!
Lots of work. Had to read and summarize every thing!
I learned so much in this class about how to do business in other countries.
Awesome professor! extremely knowledge, easy to talk to, and always available to help!

She's nice and very knowledgeable, but the class is pretty silly overall and she doesn't explain things too well. However, she does give you power points for every chapter and gives you so many free points. She curved both exams by 10% (i.e. 82 -> 92) and gave us 10 points for doing the TRACE eval, so an easy A if you participate and do the work

Annique is very knowledgeable in her field and delivers material clearly.  Debates Class participation is key to earning an A in her class.  Debates were very common and actually helped in learning the material.. Overall I enjoyed this class
She is such a great professor. She makes sure everyone participate in the class. Interesting class not boring. Two debates and one project but a lot of summaries.
If you really want to learn and are willing to put in the hours take Prof. Hashemis class. He gives very long homeworks. However if you understand the problems his exams will be breeze.
ratingTags: Respected--Lots of homework--Skip class? You won't pass.

comment: Homeworks are hours of incredibly difficult busy work. Spends the whole lecture deriving equations without any suggestion on how to use them.

spend every single minute of class time solving random examples without explaining the reason behind. keep emphasizing how easy the course would be if you follow his method while making a lot of mistakes when solving example problems.
Real good teacher, usually not hard to understand and always willing to do another example.
Very smart and conscientious. The best professor among whom I have ever met!
He threatened to fail me when I went to ask for doubts.

Hashemi knows the material well, however he teaches in a very oldschool fashion where he always demands "respect," forces you to use outdated homework software and punishes you heavily for simple mistakes that propagate easily in a class with a lot of small calculations. He drops behind on curriculum too. You'll learn but might not like him at all.
Avoid at all costs
ratingTags: Tough Grader--TEST HEAVY--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: I changed my section after the first day of class! he maybe smart, doesn't know how to talk to people, very rude! Needs to learn how to respect students! Do not take him.
As a graduate of MIT you can feel how smart he is when he is teaching. Overall you will find his courses very useful later.
A very smart teacher which knows what he is talking about

The best Professor you can have a course with if you really want to challenge yourself, go out of your comfort zone, and learn something that will be beneficial for you later in job or academia. Very nice personality, super intelligent (MIT man), while very serious in the class. You need to really read, work, and show some level of intelligence.
incredibly harsh grader, consistently gives 0's even if you have the correct answer and he doesnt like your work.

Professor Hashemi knows what he is talking about but is not very good at teaching. He expects the class to know the subject already and skips teaching new topics and goes right into doing example problems. He will use his own complicated manner to solve a problem and when a student points out an easier method he cant understand it.

He's a really nice guy and clearly really smart, but he's a poor professor. He doesn't define the syllabus and is often harsh on people who ask questions. The material itself isn't difficult it's just his teaching style. Additionally, at times he stops answering questions regardless of if there's still confusion. His grading is often times unfair.

Hashemi is a funny, sweet man and he's definitely smart but not a good professor. He will teach something once or twice in class and expect it to be learned instantly. If you go to office hours he will tell you "I taught this already. Read your book". Often solves problems incorrectly. Posted test review today that is simply incorrect.
ratingTags: Tough Grader--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--LECTURE HEAVY

comment: Had Prof. Hashemi for three different classes - an entry level FEA class, sernior level Mech Design, and a grad level mechanics of materials class. One of the most demanding professors I've had (currently a grad student and haven't had any classes nearly as hard as his). Can come off rough, but will put the effort to help you learn IF YOU DO.
Very arrogant and assumes you remember how to do everything before you start the class.

Online lectures were all out of order. He put materials that were not covered in any lectures in the exam. Arrogant inside and outside of classroom. Assumes you understand and remember everything from undergrad and would refuse to answer some of your questions. Might as well talk to a wall before you go to his office. Your'e on your own

Worst Teacher I've ever had. HW was on high-school level material. In class he solved random problems and explained nothing, and they had nothing to do with the HW. Tests were on an entirely different 3rd thing. He almost laughed at how much he didn't care about online video quality. (I was in the classroom). Rude. Wasted time talking about MIT

I would akin his lectures to an electric eel. The swiftness of his voice combined with the intensity of his electric personality combine to form a create of unmatched beauty and perfection. He talks very quickly but always answers questions and finds time to entertain his class with jokes so brilliant that, many times, even I could not comprehend.

Plays favorites and may fail you if he thinks the work you've done is not honest. Unless you're a genius he will begin to dislike you and accuse you of not listening or paying attention when he asks really obscure questions. Avoid being asked. Write your questions down, get them answered at office hours. That's where he teaches best.
No Comments
Very difficult teacher but he knows his stuff. Sometimes condescending and arrogant, but he doesn't know any better.
Hard teacher, but he knows what hes talking about. Expects a lot of work from his students but will reward you if you show you put in a real effort.

I had him for FEA and ME Design. Awesome professor. People complain about him, but he's a brilliant man often misunderstood. He's a little bit **** in the fact that he is nicer and easier to approach if you're a girl, but if you show any effort - regardless of gender - it'll turn a C into a B very easily. Respect him and he'll return the favor.

I think the people who post here (and say bad things) are probably awful students who couldn't pass Art 101 is Picasso took it for them.  If you dont understand Prof Hashemi, you should try LISTENING.

Hashemi is the man. Although he has an accent, he is very easy to understand. His teaching methods are clear and concise, and he makes great analogies to learn the material. He can tell when the class is losing interest and will tell jokes to keep everyone entertained. He was hilarious and a great teacher. I learned a lot in his classes!

He is hard to understand, and he tries to be funny, but fails to make sense.  He yells at the class constantly wasting a lot of time.  You cannot bring food or drinks to class.  Unless you suck up to him, you will have to basically teach yourself.

Rude and pompus. His lectures are incredibly fast and will insult you if you answer his questions wrong. I've visited him in his office hours a few times now and each time he has been short and unsupportive. He's a jerk. His teaching ability is standard.

Overall a good professor. Lectures are interesting and he goes on several humerous tangents about his personal life. Teaches at 100 mph, but very clear and concise. His tests are very difficult, but if you go see him he usually provides you with some valuable insight.  Likes to see students who make an effort and care about the class

This guy reminded me that NU doesn't care who they hire as long as he is an MIT grad. Really, he is pompus and arrogant and I gained little understanding from him. His test was questionable at best. On a plus note- I aced the class. But, I still don't know what I was supposed to learn, thank god for open book tests.
No Comments

Helpful at identifying what is this is and what is that is.  Very gifted teacher, he straightened out three months of mess that Rosettos made in three days of review.  Merciless grader.  Likes to play chess.

He's easy enough to follow at first and understanding him then makes it easier towards the end of the semester. Kinda harsh when it comes to answering questions. Tests were tricky but he made sure we knew what to expect.

He is extremely unhelpful and he insults you in many ways. He will never forget to remind you that he is fom MIT. His exams are unrealated to what he teaches. Read the book rather than his notes for the exam.
No Comments
Alot of work to do, starts off easy, then gets harder.  Exams are really difficult compared to class work.  He likes blueberry muffins.

She carries a charismatic and uplifting attitude into class. Most of her lectures are causal and loose, but she sticks to her agenda in the end. Also, her lectures involve a very in-depth understanding of the science of Social Psychology from both a theoretical and application perspective. The quizzes involve critical thinking so pay attention.

Professor Spikes is so funny and chill! She does go off topic sometimes to talk about family, but she still manages to stick to her agenda. Her quizzes are mainly on topics discussed in class and are based on critical thinking, but as long as you attend and take notes, its not too bad.
ratingTags: Gives good feedback--Accessible outside class--Participation matters

comment: Dont t i repeat dont take her class if you dont have to. Social psych is a great class but the way she teaches it is absolutely unbearable. She rambles a lot and cannot convey the information in a precise way which makes it impossible to pay attention.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Graded by few things

comment: Super disorganized professor, only replies to students that act like they enjoy the class, does not put effort into any lectures, does not listen to feedback, rude to students that don't say her class is the best class they have taken, syllabus did not include important days and gives out random assignments. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS.

By far the worst professor I have had at Northeastern. She is very disorganized and always makes mistakes in her slides and exam questions. This class was way more stressful than it had to be, given that the material is pretty easy. You just never know what is right or wrong since she contradicts herself all the time.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--Graded by few things

comment: Grade will be 80% based on exams that are exclusively on textbook information. Get ready to know the ins and outs of every line in the textbook. Lectures are irrelevant information not used for testing. Very disorganized and does not make time for extra help or discussion. She will assign projects very late and blames students for her mistakes.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Test heavy--Tough grader

comment: I won't recommend this professor. The course itself is so interesting; however, the way that she lectures is impossible. She once told us in class "my lectures are just an addition to the book" and, honestly, it explains everything. We are paying so much for tuition, and then it turns out that you have to study just with the book that you paid for.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Graded by few things--Test heavy

comment: She was so disorganized and offputting. I went into it really interested to learn about social psych and by the end of the semester, I was mostly frustrated and disappointed. Sorry, but it's time to put her out to pasture.

Presentation heavy, need to take good notes on lectures to pass. She talks very slow and is off topic a lot. But taking notes is important because there is some info that is important. Strict and not considerate of any circumstances if anything is late (gives 0) or if something has happened. Exams are on weekends and only have 4 things graded.
ratingTags: Skip class? You won't pass.--Graded by few things--Lecture heavy

comment: Professor Spikes is the WORST professor at northeastern. DO NOT TAKE HER CLASS. She goes off track, doesn't know anything about social psychology, literally reads off her powerpoints and takes FORVER to read. Her lectures were up to 3 hours and she explained NOTHING. I had to teach myself with the textbook. WORST PROF EVER.

Professor Spikes is absolutely hilarious. However, her lectures are often disorganized and go off-topic. Her tests are based on class material, so make sure to show up to class. She also gives out a lot of extra credit, so show up for that too. You don't need to read the textbook to get an A, but you should skim through it for the take-home tests.
Prof. Spikes is hilarious and keeps class interesting. She genuinely cares about her students and the course material.

I don't know why there are so many negative reviews. Professor Spikes is genuinely nice teacher who cares about the material she is teaching. She also really wants her students to learn and is very understanding. She is flexible and will work with you to make sure that you do well in her class and enjoy the material.

Horrible speaker. You might not think this matters, but her inability to speak her thoughts coherently makes her lectures not make sense. She just rambles on out of order or just reads off of her powerpoints. If you ask a question, she will just say "it's in your textbook". Her powerpoints are vague and confusing. You have to rely on the book.

Professor Spikes is probably the worst teacher I've ever had. She knows nothing about the material she's teaching. She simply reads off the powerpoint slides and if you ask her a question about the material, she'll deflect it because she doesn't know anything about Social Psych. The only way you'll learn anything is by reading the textbook.

Worst teacher Ive ever had. This class was extremely disorganized. Often sent multiple emails in a row changing course content. The tests were not at all what I was expecting and I felt unprepared based off the lectures. I had to teach myself all the information using the textbook and whatever random notes she gave us in class.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: I have learned NOTHING in Psychology of Women. She gathers her "lectures" 100% out of the textbook, and doesn't provide anything deeper than the surface level knowledge. Her tests are poorly worded. On our test, the majority of the students got many questions wrong because the answer was simply wrong, but she refuses to admit that she's wrong.
ratingTags: Get ready to read--Skip class? You won't pass.--GRADED BY FEW THINGS

comment: She is hilarious and she gives a lot of extra credit. I really enjoy her lectures, however, you do have to read a lot to get a good grade on the tests.

This entire course was sporadic, scatter brained & poorly outlined. The students often had no bearing of the material that would be on the exam between required readings and lectures. In addition Spikes is under informed and often rants about topics she is neither qualified nor entitled to discuss. Poorly taught and Spikes is crass & riding tenure
ratingTags: Get ready to read--GRADED BY FEW THINGS--EXTRA CREDIT

comment: She is really funny but sometimes she talks too much

Karen is a wonderful professor. Despite the fact she doesn't provide visuals, her note outlines are VERY helpful! If you write down everything she says verbatim you will do really well on the exams (or if you get notes from a classmate who does this you'll be fine). Don't show up 10 minutes late to class if you do come - she WILL call you out.

Professor Spikes is infectiously enthusiastic about the material she teaches. The lecture outlines make it so much easier to take notes and know what's important to learn, although she doesn't post study guides.  Tests can be tricky, but she throws out questions that most students get wrong and grades the article critiques generously.

I loved Professor Spikes! My favorite professor. I have her for two of my Psychology Classes back to back and I never get bored. She is funny and makes the class enjoyable. She also lets everyone share their opinion and very open to questions. Her lecture outlines are so helpful and write word to word of what she says. Tests are easy as well!

Shes really nice&funny. She has already made the outline for you and you just need to go to class and fill them out as shes talking. WARNING! Write notes down word for word, on the test shell use what she said on the outline, and in order to get full credit on the test try write things as SHE said them.
She gives really helpful lecture outlines, which is all she grades on, so you don't really need the book.
Really funny, down to earth professor. You must attend lectures if you want to pass the tests at all since all the tests are based directly off the notes from lectures.

Lectures were way too long considering Prof Spikes just reads off of a lecture outline. If you ask a question she'll reword your question for an answer. Doesn't use power points, and the humor gets really old and distracting. Studied for 40 minutes before each exam and didn't go to class, passed. Super easy. She's nice, it's just a weird atmosphere

Come to class and take notes because exams are lecture-based.  She's a very entertaining person, but the class lacked depth and inspiration. She would hand us all of the information and explain things with silly examples...  And yet I couldn't expect an A because the quizzes were so poorly worded!  Really dampened my interest in psychology.

Come to class and take notes, because the tests are based on lectures.  She is entertaining and funny, and her information is pretty straight forward.  However, I felt that the class lacked depth; that dampened my interest in psychology.  Also, the poor wording on the quizzes made it difficult for me to predict my grade despite studying well.

As long as you come to class every day and pay attention, you'll get an A. She provides lecture notes for each class, where you just fill out everything while she's talking. For the exam, she tells you exactly what will be on the exam and what specific numbers and figures you need to know. Professor Spikes is super enthusiastic and friendly as well
Easy class. Really interesting. She makes it fun. For the exams you just need to study what she tells you to study and you'll be fine.

Spikes tries to be funny and make the class laugh rather than actually teaching. She relies on the lecture outlines completely. I missed a quiz because I couldn't get back into the city after the bombing and she refused to let me make it up and gave me a zero unless I came back in the summer to take it. Easy if you do it exactly her way.

Had her for developmental (honors) and social. both classes are easy and have no finals. prof. spikes is also really funny. not exactly the best teacher ever, but she provides lecture outlines that are very relevant to the tests

Easiest class of all time. People who say that they don't like her lecture style are jacked up (as she would say). She knows her information well and knows how to make it interesting. You'll get an A if you take notes (which she makes VERY easy to take). She's a very nice person and I find her hilarious.

Spikes should not be anywhere near a classroom. class is funny at times but terribly annoying and frustrating the rest of the time. She does not know her subject, relies on cheat sheets to teach since she doesn't know the material. class is unchallenging, so easy. She does an excellent job at ruining one of the most passionate subjects in psych ...

I hadKaren Spikes  for social psych and she is a wonderful teacher. She is very helpful and hilarious. She gives plenty of extra credit. She is very strict with getting to class on time and she also doesnt like to receive unnecessary emails. I loved her class and I would definitely recommend her.

Professor Spikes is seemingly impressive. However, if you actually analyze her lecture style, you will realize that she is simply trying to be funny, and not exactly aiming to foster real learning. Initially I felt that her lectures were great, but I realized, that was just due to her southern accent being funny. I would not recommend her class.

The most inept prof here. Easily intimidated, highly unread on the subject, degrading in her teaching & boring. She plagiarizes the entire course from the book. If you want an easy A & don't mind paying 4k for what is a true insult & disgrace to proper learning, you'll fit right in. For anyone here that seeks the slightest challenge, look elsewhere

Prof. Spikes is awesome! She is really helpful and makes the class really interesting. You'll get good grades as long as you go to class, read what she tells you to and review your notes/attend the review session.  HIGHLY recommend.

I received an A in this class, but it was no thanks to Spikes. Plainly put, she is a complete lunatic. Its almost like she hates her students and she treats them like they are worthless. She is just rude and completely unhelpful. I would not take her again.

Professor Spikes is awesome! I highly recommend taking her, she really wants you to do well and gives you EXACTLY what you need to study for the tests. Her tests (in Psych of Women anyway)are all multiple choice and not difficult if you read the materials she suggests. Highly recommended, A++++

SPIKES IS AWESOME! I love her class. She makes the material easy to understand and interesting. She's funny & will make you want to go to class. She hands out note packets and tells you what parts of the book to focus on. She cares about her students & is incredibly helpful!

Spikes is a great professor.  She's so much fun and always makes class interesting.  She provides you with exactly what material you need for the tests and is very clear.  She is hilarious and makes every class fun.  She tries to get you out early when possible and is real fair in grading.  She cares about her students and is a great lady! :)

I have taken I/O, Develop., Social, & Psych of Women w/ Prof. Spikes. She is an exceptional teacher. Some people complain about her classes being a waste of time or not challenging.But she teaches you to be self disciplined &learn on your own so you can have discussions. I have learned alot from her courses. She is thorough &  to the point.

Took 4 of her classes. Don't take any of them if you are looking for DEEP discussion. HOWEVER - she makes class time effortless and funny and if you're looking for a leisurely 4 credits, take hers. Don't be fooled by her style - you need to study! Nice professor, surface-level information.
BEST TEACHER EVER!!!!!!!!

Her class is very straightforward - she hands out packets and reads off of them, occasionally filling in a sentence.  I hate this style.  It feels like I'm in middle school.  She is also not very good at answering questions probing further - often either deflecting the question to the class or just repeating the question in her answer.

Social Psych. She's a very kindhearted, intelligent and funny woman....but maybe not the most efficient professor. often gets off topic and wastes a lot of lecture time. she's a very easy professor and a lot of fun otherwise!

Professor Spikes teaches Develop., Social, Psych of Women and I/O. I've taken the first 3 and they were 3 of my favorite classes. She makes the material worth learning and her humor adds a lighter mood to the usual boring lectures. Her courses usually has 3 exams, not sure if that's changed. I/O I hear is horrible. Definitely take 1 of her classes!

Don't listen to these negative reviews. If you're laid back and have half a brain you'll love this class. If you require the teachers help for elementry school material then yeah dont take her. Spikes is a good teacher, she may be flighty sometimes but at least shes honest. In class she acts like shes just hanging out with friends.

I/O Psych.  All the notes you need are on the handouts. She's fun and a huge character, but you may learn more from the book.  The only reason I didn't have an A was  I couldn't get the hang of her tests; most MC only have 2 choices. She likes the "none of the above" answer too.
Great Teacher

I took all of Spike's classes. She hands out study guides, and you just fill in the blanks as she speaks. She's nice, funny, and experienced in the field. If you study you will get an A. but you have to go to class to get the notes.

The class is very easy. Professor Spikes is fun, and I do not find her offensive at all. If you want to be challenged and learn alot, I would not recommend this class. But if you want a fun and easy class that will get you some credits, this class is great.

This class is seriously the biggest waste of my money and time.  Karen is a HORRIBLE teacher and does not challenge you what so ever. If you like to just pay for a degree and not actually learn maybe this class is for you. She is super offensive and makes you watch terrible emotional movies with little application.  What a WASTE!
Interesting class. Spikes keeps class fun and the tests are very straight forward.

Knows material well, but does not come to class prepared to teach it.  She's absurdly offensive and inappropriate sometimes to the point where you may want to just walk out of the class.  The class was essentially common sense and not in any way intellectually challenging.  Try to take it with someone else if at all possible.

She's so amusing, and making class fun. Her psych 101 class is hysterical. I never opened the textbook once. Just memorize the study guides thoroughly and you'll get an A. The tests are T/F and multiple choice. She legitimately will tell you what's on the test a few days before. I feel like most of the material is common sense.

I just finished my 3rd course with her and she is awesome!  If you go to class and take notes on the outlines she gives you it is hard to not get an A.  She keeps you entertained and engaged in lectures.

This class is offensively bad. If you have ever been unprepared for a presentation and figured you would just B.S. through it with the little knowledge you have, you know what Karen Spikes feels like every day. All she does is read off of a packet, even then she doesn't seem to know what is happening. Horribly ambiguous test questions as well.

Fantastic professor.  Best teacher i've had at NU.  this is a good class, she types up the notes for you, tells you ahead of time what is on tests and what reading needs to be done specifically.  great teacher, knows her stuff keeps you listening!
Incompetent. Doesn't seem to have any knowledge of the subject despite having a PhD. Can't answer questions without getting confused and frustrated.

Interesting class and very easy, but she is so unorganized it's really frustrating. She just expected that we didn't do our homework every time she assigned something! You can tell being a professor is far from her main priority.

This is one of the best teachers I have ever had in my entire life. She teaches well, gives you typed notes, she is hilarious and class is very interesting. Class is not easy and you do have to try to get an A.  She is very clear and prepares you very well for the test. You will leave this class with the knowledge necessary to be an amazing parent.

Spikes is awesome.  She tells you everything you need to know for the exams and tells you what to avoid studying.  She's from the south and jokes around a lot in class.  She's a riot.  Take her class.

Just completed my second class with Professor Spikes and I would definitely take more if I could. I completely disagree that she is not a "real" professor. She's very knowledgeable of the subjects and integrates learning into a more relaxed and interesting environment. I've definitely learned more in her classes than in some boring lectures.

I disagree with the comment below me. Spikes is an incredible teacher. I have her for Developmental right now and I've learned so much about the subject. She's funny, keeps the class alive and appreciates our opinions. There's only 3 exams, no midterm or final. Notes are type written for you and she gives extra credit at the end. She's awesome.

Professor Spikes is probably one of the greatest teachers' i've had, no BS. She gives type written handouts and prepares you very well for her exams. Btw there is no midterm/final. I dont consider it an easy class, you do have to put effort into taking notes and understanding the material. I'm definitely taking her Social Psych class next semester.

She was an awesome professor.  The class wasn't boring which might have had to do with taking it during the summer.  Grading system is set up in a way where you can easily get an A.  2 writing assignments and 2 tests.  Definitely take here for Intro to Psychology.
Excellent!

Best professor for PSY U101. This was my third time taking this course and she is better than both of the other professors (Snyder, and a guest professor). Attend all classes, follow along with her outlines, and interact to get an easy A+.

Great prof with an easy-going/humorous personality. Her lectures are interesting, extremely helpful notes.  I've really learned a lot from her. Pay attention in class and use her notes, sometimes the textbook to help you understand the materials, and you'll do well on exams!

This woman has no place in the classroom.  She is meant for the business world and should have stayed there.  Her classes consist of handing out an outline and then reading it to you and filling in some trivia she brings up.   Unwilling to help you with office hours or missed tests, her time is too valuable....
I really enjoyed this class. As long as you show up to class and fill in the outlined notes, the tests will be pretty easy and straightforward. She is a good teacher and she is pretty amusing.

I didn't buy the book or study and made an A. She doesn't seem to be very bright at all and is condescending to anyone who provokes a subject beyond the text. I many times believed that she didn't know what she was talking about and became extremely confused and aggravated when questioned. If you know how to read you're qualified for her position.

Her class is ridiculously easy, but she does include questions on that test that she expects you to read from the book the night before (the only time you use it) and has never discussed in class.  She can also be pretty disrespectful...she's funny, but sometimes you really want to **** her out.
Very easy professor. She prints and gives out handouts for all her lectures. Her tests are really easy and she always cuts down the reading to almost none. Very easy going and willing to help.
Very easy class, super nice professor. Someone interesting subject; however, most of the material is common sense. I definitely enjoyed this class though, and the easy A.
Very fun and interactive despite going through two foot surgeries.

comment: Definitely one of my favorite professors at Northeastern. Prof Golden is always ready to teach. He devotes a great level of energy to class and always inspires his students. The feedback he provides is solid and detailed. I had lots of takeaways and would recommend taking his class!

He really took advantage of the online learning by bringing in fantastic professionals to guest speak to us. Great professor, highly recommended.

the whole class is based on the group project, where you come up with a product and go through the lean design process. I took Innovation! with him on-campus and it was a great experience. I can't say the same about the online Lean Design. Assignment instructions were very unclear and vague. Be prepared to go hunting for grading rubrics/guidelines.
Great Professor and one of a kind business mentor. Take his class if you want to be challenged and inspired.

You definitely have to work hard in this class, but Prof Golden is a great professor and all around person. He really inspires and motivates his students, and is available for help and feedback when your group needs it.

comment: Chuck Fountain is one of the most enthusiastic and passionate professors I've ever had. He is very well-read and a great lecturer. Don't expect to get a word in during his classes though.
